The only thing exotic about this place are the flies flying around your food. If you are looking for authentic Indian food...venture elsewhere. The curry plate ordered was merely canned tomato paste with black pepper.  The tandoori chicken tasted like your weekend BBQ chicken without the BBQ. The rice was undercooked. Our drinks were never refilled. We were not asked if our meal was to our liking or if we needed anything else. We had to wait 45 mins for a entree, meanwhile other Indian families were given the preferred treatment.  Never again! We are out $50 and still hungry! And
